## 1. Purpose
This document establishes [COMPANY]'s policy for the permitted uses and disclosures of Protected Health Information (PHI), summarizes the privacy rights of individuals, and defines [COMPANY]'s obligations regarding the Notice of Privacy Practices (NPP) under the HIPAA Privacy Rule (45 CFR § 164.520). It ensures PHI is used and disclosed only as permitted or required by law, and that individuals are informed of how their information is handled.

## 2. Scope
Applies to all PHI that [COMPANY] creates, receives, maintains, or transmits in any form (electronic, paper, verbal), across all workforce members, contractors, and in-scope systems including the production SaaS application, [AWS environment], [Snowflake], and the [GitHub] CI/CD pipeline.

## 3. Role Determination — Covered Entity vs. Business Associate
[COMPANY]'s privacy obligations depend on its role for a given data flow. **This determination drives whether an NPP must be published (see §4).**

| Role | NPP Obligation | Summary |
|---|---|---|
| **Business Associate (BA)** | Does **not** issue its own NPP | [COMPANY] handles PHI on behalf of Covered Entities. It must use/disclose PHI only as the BAA and the Privacy Rule permit, and must honor the limits in each CE's NPP. |
| **Covered Entity (CE)** | **Must** publish and maintain an NPP per § 164.520 | If [COMPANY] acts as a CE for any line of business, it must produce, distribute, and post a compliant NPP. |

1. [COMPANY] **shall** document, with counsel, its HIPAA role for each product/data flow and record it in [the data flow inventory / record of processing].
2. Where [COMPANY] is a BA, it **shall** not make uses or disclosures of PHI that the originating Covered Entity's NPP would not permit.

## 4. Notice of Privacy Practices (Covered Entity obligations — 45 CFR § 164.520)
<!-- TEMPLATE: Only complete this section if [COMPANY] acts as a Covered Entity. If purely a BA, mark N/A and retain §3 + §5. -->
Where [COMPANY] acts as a Covered Entity, it **shall** maintain an NPP that, at minimum:
1. Is written in **plain language** and contains the required **header** stated in § 164.520(b)(1)(i) substantially as: *"THIS NOTICE DESCRIBES HOW MEDICAL INFORMATION ABOUT YOU MAY BE USED AND DISCLOSED AND HOW YOU CAN GET ACCESS TO THIS INFORMATION. PLEASE REVIEW IT CAREFULLY."*
2. Describes the **uses and disclosures** of PHI permitted without authorization (treatment, payment, health care operations) with at least one example of each, and categories requiring authorization.
3. States that **uses/disclosures not described require written authorization**, and that the individual may **revoke** an authorization.
4. Describes the individual's **rights** (see §6) and how to exercise them.
5. States [COMPANY]'s **legal duties** to protect PHI and to abide by the terms of the current notice.
6. Provides a **point of contact** for complaints and the right to complain to [COMPANY] and to HHS/OCR **without retaliation**.
7. States an **effective date** and reserves the right to **change** the notice and apply changes to previously created PHI.
8. Is **provided** to individuals (at first service delivery and on request), **posted** prominently on any website and at physical service sites, and a **good-faith effort** is made to obtain written acknowledgment of receipt where direct treatment applies.

## 5. Permitted Uses & Disclosures of PHI
1. PHI **shall** be used or disclosed only as permitted by the Privacy Rule or as required by law, and limited to the **minimum necessary** except where the minimum necessary standard does not apply (see `minimum-necessary-standard.md.template`).
2. Uses/disclosures for **Treatment, Payment, and Health Care Operations (TPO)** are permitted as defined at 45 CFR § 164.506, subject to the originating CE's NPP and the BAA where [COMPANY] is a BA.
3. Disclosures **required by law** (e.g., to HHS for compliance, in response to valid legal process) **shall** be made only after verification of the requestor and, where required, consultation with [Legal / Counsel].
4. Uses/disclosures **not** covered above (e.g., marketing, sale of PHI, most psychotherapy notes) **shall** be made only with a valid, signed **authorization** meeting 45 CFR § 164.508.
5. PHI **shall not** be used or disclosed for purposes outside the BAA (where [COMPANY] is a BA) — including product analytics, model training, or new features — without confirming the use is permitted; see `de-identification-and-limited-data-set.md.template` for analytics/AI pathways.

## 6. Summary of Individual Rights
The following rights are summarized here and operationalized in `individual-rights-procedure.md.template`:
| Right | Reference |
|---|---|
| Access to and a copy of PHI | 45 CFR § 164.524 |
| Amendment of PHI | 45 CFR § 164.526 |
| Accounting of disclosures | 45 CFR § 164.528 |
| Request restrictions on uses/disclosures | 45 CFR § 164.522(a) |
| Confidential communications | 45 CFR § 164.522(b) |
| Receive a paper copy of the NPP | 45 CFR § 164.520(c) |
| Complain without retaliation | 45 CFR § 164.520(b)(1)(vi) |

As a Business Associate, [COMPANY] **shall** support the relevant Covered Entity in honoring these rights per the BAA, typically by routing requests to the CE and providing data/responses within agreed timelines.

## 7. Contact & Complaints
1. Privacy questions, requests, and complaints are directed to the [Privacy Officer] at [privacy contact — email / phone / address].
2. Individuals **shall** be able to complain without fear of retaliation, and **shall** be informed of their right to complain to HHS/OCR.
3. Where [COMPANY] is a BA, individual-facing inquiries are generally redirected to the originating Covered Entity per the BAA.

## 8. Roles & Responsibilities
| Role | Responsibility |
|---|---|
| [Privacy Officer] | Owns this policy and the NPP (if a CE); approves permitted-use determinations; handles complaints. |
| [Security Officer] | Implements technical controls enforcing permitted uses/disclosures and minimum necessary. |
| [Legal / Counsel] | Confirms NPP content, role determinations, and authorization requirements. |
| All Workforce | Use/disclose PHI only as permitted; route requests and complaints to the Privacy Officer. |

See `../governance/roles-and-responsibilities.md.template` for full role definitions.

## 9. Exceptions
Exceptions to this policy require documented risk acceptance per `../governance/exceptions-and-waivers.md.template`, approved by the [Privacy Officer] and [General Counsel], time-bound, and recorded in the exceptions log. Statutory NPP content and distribution requirements **may not** be waived by internal exception.

## 10. Compliance, Monitoring & Enforcement
Compliance is monitored through privacy audits, review of disclosure logs, and management review. The [Privacy Officer] verifies the NPP (if applicable) remains current and properly distributed/posted. Violations are handled per `../people/hr-security-policy.md.template` and the HIPAA workforce sanctions process (`sanctions-policy.md.template`).

